The paper discusses a novel probabilistic programming language framework that couples with existing scientific simulators and provides efficient inference engines. This involves the use of deep learning-based inference compilation and distributed training on a supercomputer. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Additionally, the paper also discusses software engineering aspects such as cross-platform execution protocol and enhancements to PyTorch, which makes cs.SE (Software Engineering) a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper also presents a use-case with the Large Hadron Collider, which makes cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) a possible sub-category.
